        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). As the return from the Captivity almost exclusively affected the exiles of the Southern Kingdom, the name was naturally applied to the new dwellers in Jerusalem and the neighbourhood, and was quickly adopted as the designation of all members of the race; cf. ",
        "children": []
